cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for human activity recognition from low-resolution videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new concept of inverse super resolution, which involves learning the optimal set of image transformations to generate multiple low-resolution training videos from a single video. This concept is related to machine learning and optimization, which could fall under cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence). The paper also addresses privacy concerns related to surreptitious video recordings, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
